              "ClinicalWarningAgencyCode": {
                "Value": "EUDAMED"
              },
              "ClinicalWarningCode": "CW999",
              "WarningsOrContraIndicationDescription": [
                {
                  "LanguageCode": "en",
                  "Value": "Do not exceed stimulation energy rating in Cable Specifications as this may damage connected 3rd party leads. \n•\tDo not use the cable for connecting life-supportive pacing. For life support, always connect pacing leads directly to pacing devices. \n•\tPlease refer to technical manual of the particular devices before coupling them together.\n•\tDo not expose the cables to storage temperatures other than specified in “Permissible Environmental Conditions”\n•\tCheck package before use. Damaged packages should be returned to Micropace.\n•\tInspect cable prior to use and do not use if visibly damaged with kinks, cuts to insulation, exposed inner cables or wires or if packaging is damaged.\n•\tDo not modify the cable. Cable may not be physically modified. Modifications may reduce system effectiveness.\n•\tIn order to avoid risk of infection, do not use cable which appears soiled, contaminated or is not indicated to have been cleaned between uses according to cleaning instructions.\n•\tDo not allow the cable to come into contact with open wounds.\n•\tConnect cable only to equipment with connections of type CF and defibrillator proof.\n•\tDo not connect to any cables or equipment with exposed wires or connectors subject to human touch or contact with conductive surfaces.\n•\tAlways observe polarity and chamber designations when coupling multiple devices. \n•\tDo not force connector into a port of coupled device.\n•\tAny serious incident that occurs in relation to this device should be reported to Micropace and to the relevant local regulatory authority.\n"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      },
